{
  "texts": [
    "Yuan et al. (2020) defined the de-pooling operation as the inverse of the pooling operation.",
    "The structure of the method is completed with spectral graph convolutions from (Defferrard et al. 2016) instead of fully connected layers.",
    "This method is expanded by the possibility to generate shapes, by implementing a Conditional Variational Autoencoder (CVAE) architecture, where the user defines the parameters that must be taken into account when generating a new shape.",
    "Also at the input, this method uses vertex-based deformation feature representation (Gao et al. 2019).",
    "While Yuan et al. (2020) produce better quality meshes than (Garland and Heckbert 1997), only homogeneous meshes are processable due to the mesh simplification-based pooling."
  ]
}